# /sync-design — Load Voting Protocol Design Context

When this rule is invoked, load the protocol design from the shielded_vote_book and confirm what you retrieved.

## 1. Read the AI index first

```
docs/shielded-vote-book-index.md
```

This is a condensed structural index of the entire shielded_vote_book. It contains per-file summaries and section maps so you can identify which files to read for a given topic without ingesting the full book.

## 2. Read specific book sections as needed

The full protocol spec lives in the symlinked Obsidian vault at `shielded_vote_book/`. Key entry points:

- **`shielded_vote_book/SUMMARY.md`** — Table of contents (all chapters)
- **`shielded_vote_book/overview/`** — Design principles, overall flow, privacy guarantees
- **`shielded_vote_book/data-types.md`** — VAN, VC, Vote Share, VCT definitions
- **`shielded_vote_book/circuits/overview.md`** — Circuit component map (which gadgets are used where)
- **`shielded_vote_book/zkps/`** — Per-ZKP specs (ZKP #1, #2, #3)
- **`shielded_vote_book/chain/`** — Vote chain role, ceremony, API
- **`shielded_vote_book/delegation/`** — Delegation setup, partial delegation, server shares
- **`shielded_vote_book/appendices/`** — El Gamal, tally, PIR

Only read the specific files relevant to your current task — do not ingest the entire book.

## 3. If the symlink is missing

If `shielded_vote_book/` does not exist in the workspace root, tell the user:

> The `shielded_vote_book` symlink is not present. Please create it:
> ```
> ln -s /path/to/your/shielded_vote_book shielded_vote_book
> ```
> See `docs/ai_setup.md` for details.

## After loading

Summarize which sections you loaded and confirm the sources are available. Then ask how to proceed.
